WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:29.000
To survive the hospital blueprint, you must develop 'Range.' As a clinician, you were trained on the track — a 'Kind' environment, where the rules are clear and the hurdles are visible. But system innovation is the jungle. It's a 'Wicked' environment, where the variables constantly change. You can't bring track shoes to a jungle. You must be functionally flexible — willing to drop your specialized clinical tools and pick up a machete, or a compass, when the environment demands it.
